      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Arcade.dev"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Arcade.dev is a tool execution platform that provides a catalog of 100+ pre-built tools, a managed auth engine for user-delegated OAuth, and a sandboxed execution environment for running tool code. Where Composio focuses on SaaS workflow automation, Arcade places particular emphasis on human-in-the-loop authorization \u2014 a user can approve or reject a sensitive action before it executes \u2014 making it suited for agents that act on behalf of individual users with high-stakes permissions."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Arcade architecture: agent calls client.tools.list and client.tools.execute through the Arcade engine which manages auth and dispatches to external APIs",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Arcade's standout feature is its built-in human-in-the-loop authorization gate. When a tool requires explicit user approval, Arcade pauses execution and waits for the user to accept or reject \u2014 without you writing any approval flow code."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Installation and Setup"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "pip install arcadepy anthropic\n\n# Set your Arcade API key\nexport ARCADE_API_KEY=\"arc_...\"\nexport ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=\"sk-ant-...\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Listing and Using Arcade Tools"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Arcade exposes tools through a Python SDK. You retrieve the tool catalog as Claude-compatible schemas and pass them directly to the messages API."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import os\nimport anthropic\nfrom arcadepy import Arcade\n\narcade = Arcade(api_key=os.environ[\"ARCADE_API_KEY\"])\nclaude = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\n# List all available tools as Claude-compatible schemas\ntools = arcade.tools.list(format=\"anthropic\")\n\nprint(f\"Available tools: {len(tools)}\")\nfor t in tools[:5]:\n    print(f\"  {t['name']}: {t['description'][:60]}\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Running an Agent with Arcade"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import os, anthropic\nfrom arcadepy import Arcade\n\narcade = Arcade(api_key=os.environ[\"ARCADE_API_KEY\"])\nclaude = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\n# Filter to just the tools you need for this task\ngithub_tools = arcade.tools.list(toolkit=\"github\", format=\"anthropic\")\n\ndef run_agent(user_id: str, task: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Run an agent that can use Arcade-managed GitHub tools on behalf of user_id.\n    user_id is used by Arcade to look up the user's connected OAuth tokens.\n    \"\"\"\n    messages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": task}]\n\n    while True:\n        resp = claude.messages.create(\n            model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n            max_tokens=1024,\n            tools=github_tools,\n            messages=messages,\n        )\n\n        if resp.stop_reason == \"end_turn\":\n            return next(b.text for b in resp.content if hasattr(b, \"text\"))\n\n        messages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": resp.content})\n        results = []\n\n        for block in resp.content:\n            if block.type != \"tool_use\":\n                continue\n\n            # Arcade executes the tool using the user's stored credentials\n            execution = arcade.tools.execute(\n                tool_name=block.name,\n                inputs=block.input,\n                user_id=user_id,\n            )\n\n            # execution.output contains the result; execution.requires_auth is\n            # True when the user needs to authorise this tool for the first time\n            if execution.requires_auth:\n                auth_url = execution.authorization_url\n                results.append({\n                    \"type\": \"tool_result\",\n                    \"tool_use_id\": block.id,\n                    \"content\": (\n                        f\"This action requires the user to authorise GitHub access. \"\n                        f\"Direct them to: {auth_url}\"\n                    ),\n                })\n            else:\n                results.append({\n                    \"type\": \"tool_result\",\n                    \"tool_use_id\": block.id,\n                    \"content\": str(execution.output),\n                })\n\n        messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": results})\n\n# Example\nresult = run_agent(\"user_alice\", \"List the open issues in my repo anthropics/anthropic-sdk-python\")\nprint(result)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "execution.requires_auth"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "True"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", Arcade has detected that the user has not yet connected their account (or the token has expired). The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "authorization_url"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is the OAuth consent URL to redirect the user to."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Human-in-the-Loop Authorization"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For sensitive actions \u2014 sending an email, posting publicly, deleting data \u2014 Arcade can require explicit user approval before the tool runs. The agent pauses, presents the approval request, and waits for the user's decision."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import os, time\nfrom arcadepy import Arcade\n\narcade = Arcade(api_key=os.environ[\"ARCADE_API_KEY\"])\n\ndef execute_with_approval(\n    tool_name: str,\n    inputs: dict,\n    user_id: str,\n    timeout_seconds: float = 60.0,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Execute a tool that may require user approval.\n    Polls the approval status until the user responds or the timeout expires.\n    \"\"\"\n    execution = arcade.tools.execute(\n        tool_name=tool_name,\n        inputs=inputs,\n        user_id=user_id,\n    )\n\n    if not execution.requires_approval:\n        return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": execution.output}\n\n    # Present the approval URL to the user (in a real app, show in UI)\n    print(f\"Approval required: {execution.approval_url}\")\n\n    deadline = time.monotonic() + timeout_seconds\n    while time.monotonic() < deadline:\n        status = arcade.tools.get_execution(execution.id)\n        if status.status == \"approved\":\n            return {\"ok\": True, \"output\": status.output}\n        if status.status == \"rejected\":\n            return {\n                \"ok\": False,\n                \"error\": \"USER_REJECTED\",\n                \"message\": \"The user rejected this action\",\n            }\n        if status.status == \"failed\":\n            return {\n                \"ok\": False,\n                \"error\": \"EXECUTION_FAILED\",\n                \"message\": status.error or \"Tool execution failed\",\n            }\n        time.sleep(2)\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": False,\n        \"error\": \"TIMEOUT\",\n        \"message\": f\"User did not respond within {timeout_seconds} seconds\",\n    }\n\n# Usage in agent loop\nresult = execute_with_approval(\n    tool_name=\"Google.SendEmail\",\n    inputs={\"to\": \"team@example.com\", \"subject\": \"Weekly report\", \"body\": \"...\"},\n    user_id=\"user_alice\",\n)\nif result[\"ok\"]:\n    print(\"Email sent:\", result[\"output\"])\nelse:\n    print(\"Not sent:\", result[\"error\"])\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Filtering Toolkits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Arcade organises tools into toolkits by service. Fetching only the relevant toolkit keeps the tool list manageable and improves model selection accuracy."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from arcadepy import Arcade\n\narcade = Arcade(api_key=os.environ[\"ARCADE_API_KEY\"])\n\n# Available toolkits include: github, google, slack, spotify, x, notion, jira, ...\ngithub_tools   = arcade.tools.list(toolkit=\"github\",  format=\"anthropic\")\ngdrive_tools   = arcade.tools.list(toolkit=\"google\",  format=\"anthropic\")\nslack_tools    = arcade.tools.list(toolkit=\"slack\",   format=\"anthropic\")\n\nprint(f\"GitHub tools:  {len(github_tools)}\")\nprint(f\"Google tools:  {len(gdrive_tools)}\")\nprint(f\"Slack tools:   {len(slack_tools)}\")\n\n# Combine specific toolkits for a task-specific agent\nresearch_tools = github_tools + gdrive_tools\ncollab_tools   = slack_tools + github_tools\n\n# Or fetch a specific tool by name\nspecific = arcade.tools.list(tool_name=\"GitHub.CreateIssue\", format=\"anthropic\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
