      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Custom Tool Registration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Beyond the built-in toolkits, Arcade lets you register your own tools using the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "@arcade.tool"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " decorator. Custom tools run in Arcade's sandboxed environment with the same auth, audit, and HITL capabilities as built-in ones."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# my_tools.py\nimport arcade\nfrom arcade.sdk import ToolContext\n\n@arcade.tool(\n    name=\"crm.get_contact\",\n    description=\"Look up a CRM contact by email address.\",\n    inputs={\n        \"email\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\",\n            \"description\": \"The contact email address.\"\n        }\n    }\n)\ndef get_contact(ctx: ToolContext, email: str) -> dict:\n    import requests\n    resp = requests.get(\n        \"https://api.yourcrm.com/contacts\",\n        params={\"email\": email},\n        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {ctx.secrets['CRM_API_KEY']}\"},\n        timeout=10,\n    )\n    resp.raise_for_status()\n    contact = resp.json()\n    return {\n        \"id\": contact[\"id\"],\n        \"name\": contact[\"full_name\"],\n        \"company\": contact[\"company\"],\n        \"plan\": contact.get(\"plan\", \"unknown\"),\n    }\n\n# Register the tool with your Arcade deployment:\n# arcade tools register my_tools:get_contact\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "ctx.secrets"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " dict is populated from Arcade's vault at execution time, so credentials never appear in source code or agent prompts."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Audit Logs and Tracing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every tool call Arcade executes is recorded with user identity, inputs (excluding secrets), result status, and timestamp. Retrieve recent executions via the API for compliance reporting or debugging:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from arcadepy import Arcade\n\narcade = Arcade()\n\n# List the last 50 executions for a user\nexecutions = arcade.executions.list(user_id=\"user_42\", limit=50)\n\nfor ex in executions.items:\n    status = \"OK\" if ex.success else \"FAIL\"\n    print(f\"[{status}] {ex.tool_name:40s} {ex.executed_at}\")\n\n# Drill into a single execution\ndetail = arcade.executions.get(executions.items[0].id)\n    print(\"Inputs :\", detail.inputs)\n    print(\"Output :\", detail.output)\n    print(\"Duration:\", detail.duration_ms, \"ms\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The execution log is also surfaced in the Arcade dashboard, where administrators can review individual tool calls, replay failed executions, and configure retention policies."
          }
        ]
